overview:
iambic, Inc. is an independent software vendor (ISV) of productivity-enhancing software applications for Palm OS, Windows Mobile Pocket PC, Windows Mobile Smartphone, Symbian UIQ and BlackBerry mobile platforms as well as Microsoft Windows desktop and notebook platforms.

iambic’s best-known software applications are:

  • Agendus: application for managing personal information, and communications for Palm, Treo, Windows Mobile, UIQ, and Windows Desktop.
  • Agendus Mail: email and text messaging client for Palm OS
  • Health & Diet Manager: personal health and diet management solution for Windows Mobile.
  • Propel: application launcher tool for Palm OS.
  • TopStory: RSS reader available for Palm OS and Windows Mobile
  • Vehicle Manager: automotive tracking application for Windows Mobile and Windows Desktop.
  • YourCall: phone call management tool for Palm OS-based Treos

Funded in 1994, iambic, Inc. is a privately held corporation headquartered in Sunnyvale, California. The company sells their applications directly and through resellers.
